HEADWORD: Petrifactive
<hw>Pet`ri*fac"tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having the quality of converting organic matter into stone;
petrifying.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pertaining to, or characterized by,
petrifaction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The . . . <qex>petrifactive</qex> mutations of hard bodies.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir T. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Petrific</ent>⟦br⟧
